The paper focuses on the modeling and analysis of highly (re)configurable systems, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a formal modeling language and statistical model checking techniques, which are relevant to the logic in computer science (cs.LO) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of probabilistic behavior and feature constraints, which are relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
